                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17575612" author="oholzma" created="Fri, 5 Aug 2022 07:10:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;ProxyHttpClientConfigurer&lt;/tt&gt; needs to set the proxy credentials for the auth scope of the proxy &lt;tt&gt;HttpHost&lt;/tt&gt; instead of &lt;tt&gt;AuthScope.ANY&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;and it must add new credential to a potentially existing &lt;tt&gt;credentialsProvider&lt;/tt&gt; of &lt;tt&gt;clientBuilder&lt;/tt&gt;; currently &lt;tt&gt;ProxyHttpClientConfigurer&lt;/tt&gt; overwrites the &lt;tt&gt;credentialsProvider&lt;/tt&gt; of &lt;tt&gt;clientBuilder&lt;/tt&gt; provided by &lt;tt&gt;BasicAuthenticationHttpClientConfigurer&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="17575623" author="davsclaus" created="Fri, 5 Aug 2022 07:48:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You are welcome to work on a PR as you can then also test the code changes in your system&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17582964" author="klease78" created="Mon, 22 Aug 2022 13:08:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=OHolzma&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;OHolzma&quot;&gt;OHolzma&lt;/a&gt; If you aren&apos;t planning to submit a PR for this, I can propose one based on&#160; your analysis.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17583116" author="oholzma" created="Mon, 22 Aug 2022 17:37:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=klease78&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;klease78&quot;&gt;klease78&lt;/a&gt; please feel free to create a fix. I&apos;m happy support &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17584161" author="klease78" created="Wed, 24 Aug 2022 10:09:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have submitted the PR if you want to try it out. I added a unit test which reproduced the issue and which works after the change.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17585149" author="davsclaus" created="Fri, 26 Aug 2022 04:38:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you backport this to 3.18.x branch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
